# Bart provider secrets — server-side ONLY.
#
# Copy to `.env` and fill in a key for whichever provider you're testing.
# Never use a client-exposed prefix (VITE_ / NEXT_PUBLIC_): these are read by
# server code only. `.env` is gitignored; this example file is safe to commit.
#
# The registry itself reads NONE of these — provider keys are the consumer
# server's concern. `bun run scripts/dev-real.ts` (local smoke test) and the
# future `@bart-ui/cli`-generated server code load them.

# Google Gemini (default for the local smoke test).
# The @ai-sdk/google adapter reads GOOGLE_GENERATIVE_AI_API_KEY on its own;
# the smoke-test launcher also accepts GEMINI_API_KEY / GOOGLE_API_KEY.
#GOOGLE_GENERATIVE_AI_API_KEY=

# OpenAI — used by `--provider openai`.
# OPENAI_API_KEY=

# Anthropic (Claude) — used by `--provider anthropic`.
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
